@node Preferences
@chapter Changing default behaviour of FlexCat
@cindex Preferences
@cindex flexcat.prefs

Since version 1.9 FlexCat implements simple preference mechanism.
By using environmental variable @var{FLEXCAT.PREFS} you can change
program's default behaviour.

Variable @var{FLEXCAT.PREFS} is parsed using dos.library ReadArgs()
call, thus all switches should be typed in one line with space
as switch separator. The preferences template looks as follow:
@example

SDDIR/K,NEW_MSG/K,WARNCTGAPS/S,NOOPTIM/S,FILL/S,FLUSH/S,NOBEEP/S,QUIET/S,
COPYMSGNEW/S,OLDMSGNEW/K/,NOSPACE/S

@end example

@table @strong
@cindex NEW_MSG
@item NEW_MSG
can be used to customize the text, FlexCat uses to mark new strings
apparing while updating the catalog translation file (using new description
file and old translation). The default string is @var{***NEW***}.

For detailed information about other tags, please read the @ref{Program start}
chapter.

Note concerning SDDIR: while creating source file FlexCat firstly check
the current dir, then directory set in preferences. If it still fails,
it read @var{FLEXCAT_SDDIR} variable and finally the @file{"PROGDIR:lib/"}
drawer. So using both preferences variable and @var{FLEXCAT_SDDIR} you
can use two custom descriptors' drawers simultaneously.

