defined to avoid multiple symols etc. In few words: use
@samp{%b} as prefix, suffix or other part of any name that
is the vital part of source. If you table of strings is
named @samp{STRING} replace this by @samp{%b_STRINGS} and
you won't get dublicated lables any longer.

@samp{CatComp_h.sd} produces source file similar to CatComp's
used to generate, and can be used by those people who wish to
use FlexCat but don't want to significantly change all of own
programs.

